dc:contributor  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_997  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig1 shows by quantitative immunoEM that NFM (neurofilament medium) is mainly present in the postsynapse with also significant labelling in the presynapse compared to background labeling in mitochondria (Fig1b). Fig1A, C and D show typical examples. Similar finding are reported using fluorescence microscopy where NFM colocalises with postsynaptic marker PSD95 (Fig1g) and presynaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig1h). FigS2E shows NFM labelling by pre-embedding methods, which is quantified against the neurofilament triple knockout (FigS2i) showing that the antibody is specific.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Adult male or female mice of the C57BL/6J-rich strain, aged 3 - 12 months were used in all experiments.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_997" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

